<doc id="483121" wikidata="Q7315726" url="?curid=483121" title="Resolving power">
<text>Resolving power is the capacity of an instrument to resolve two points which are close together.

Specifically, resolving power may refer to:

* Angular resolution
* Spectral resolution
* Optical resolution
* Resolution (mass spectrometry)

